i men and their experiences as combat soldiers in the Israeli Defense Forces (IDF), particularly those who served in the “Occupied Palestinian Territories” (OPT) during the “Al Aqsa Intifada,” which broke out in 2000. In describing the soldiers’ circumstances, especially focusing on space, the study shows how processes of numbing on different levels influence the (moral) behavior of these soldiers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aAl-Aqsa Intifada, 2000-xAtrocities. 0aApathy. 0aHuman rightszGaza Strip. 0aHuman rightszGaza strip. 0aHuman rightszIsrael. 0aHuman rightszWest Bank. 0aMilitary ethicszIsrael. 0aMilitary governmentzIsrael. 0aSoldierszIsraelxAttitudes. 0aSoldierszIsraelxMoral conditions. 0aSoldierszIsraelxSocial conditions. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745957240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857459572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857459572/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK